    "Jason Murray is the cofounder, chairman and CEO of Utah-based PACS Group, a publicly traded firm that operates skilled nursing facilities.",
    "He cofounded PACS Group with fellow billionaire Mark Hancock in 2013 and the pair took the company public on the New York Stock Exchange in 2024.",
    "PACS Group started with two skilled nursing facilities and has since expanded to 315 facilities in 17 states in the U.S.",
    "Murray and Hancock each owned 50% of PACS Group before the IPO; Murray now owns nearly 35% of the company's shares.",
    "Before starting PACS, Murray worked as a healthcare executive and licensed nursing home administrator."
